Why on earth would it be "error handling". This just assumes that the developer for some reason throws some exception if there's no match for a username or password, what a silly assumption, as this logic is generally done in the body of a method (but could be done either way).
A very general code example would be:
private Boolean isValidUser(String user, String password){
if(dao.verifyUser(user) && dao.verifyPassword(password){
 return true;
}
else{
 addMessage("Your credentials were not correct");
 return false;
}

How is it possible that Comptia is taken seriously by anybody in this field?
